Confidentiality | Integrity | Availability

The most crucial information security components and should be 
guaranted in any secure system.

Confidentiality - To prevent sensitive information from reaching
		  people that should not get access to it.

Integrity - To maintain the consistency, accuracy and trustworthiness of
	    data over its entire life cycle.

Availability - Make all the information available and accessible for 
	       authorized persons whenever it is needed.

